# Comments may be added freely,  starting with #.
#
# See https://minorplanetcenter.net/mpcops/documentation/identifications/submission_format/
# for some details.  Basically,  MPC allows you to submit identifications
# as a JSON file.  The file lists the designations you've linked,  the
# orbital elements for the linkage,  and your contact information.  Whenever
# Find_Orb is fed observations with different designations,  it makes a
# 'linkage.json' file containing all that information.  You can then
# submit the file to
#
# https://minorplanetcenter.net/mpcops/submissions/identifications/
#
# You should change the name and e-mail address,  and probably the
# comment,  too.  Then rename this file to 'link_hdr.json'.  Find_Orb
# will use that instead of the default 'link_def.json'.  (And when
# you update,  your name and e-mail won't get overwritten.)
#
#    Please leave the %t and %v somewhere in the header.  Find_Orb
# will replace them with the time the linkage was written and the
# Find_Orb version date,  both of which may help in puzzling out any
# bugs or mangled linkage files.
{
  "header": {
    "name": "J. Doe",
    "email": "john_doe@example.com",
    "comment": "Default identification comment.  Linkage written %t UTC.  Find_Orb version %v."
  },
